15/07/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivo Sanader met on Thursday (14 July) with leaders of the Croatian Employers Union (HUP) to discuss the latest economic developments in the country.
Sanader said he hopes Croatia will open accession talks with the EU soon, but assured HUP that even if they are delayed, the government will not slow the pace of reforms and will continue with infrastructure projects, judicial reforms and the pursuit of higher living standards.
Also Thursday, Croatian President Stipe Mesic kicked off a two-day visit to Kiev, where he met with Ukrainian counterpart Viktor Yushchenko.
They focused on efforts to enhance bilateral trade and economic co-operation and vowed to launch talks on lifting visa requirements.
(Vecernji List - 15/07/05;
HINA - 14/07/05)
